===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang}} {{term|hūsbonda||lang=ang|male head of a household}}, probably derived from {{ON.}} {{term|húsbóndi||lang=non|master of house}}, from ''[[hús]]'' ("house") and ''[[bóndi]]'' ("dweller", "householder"). Cognate with Faroese and Icelandic ''[[húsbóndi]]'' and Norwegian ''[[husbond]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-husband.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[man]] in a marriage or marital relationship.
# Large [[cushion]] with arms meant to support a person in the sitting position.
#: ''While reading her book, Sally leaned back against her '''husband''', wishing it were the human kind.''

